{"name": "opentelemetry-instrumentation-vertexai", "metadata": {"name": "opentelemetry-instrumentation-vertexai", "version": "0.33.12", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Apache Software License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/traceloop/openllmetry/tree/main/packages/opentelemetry-instrumentation-vertexai", "license": "Apache-2.0", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["opentelemetry-api", "opentelemetry-instrumentation", "opentelemetry-semantic-conventions", "opentelemetry-semantic-conventions-ai"], "summary": "OpenTelemetry Vertex AI instrumentation", "upload_time": 1731529665}, "documentation": ["# OpenTelemetry VertexAI Instrumentation\n\n<a href=\"https://pypi.org/project/opentelemetry-instrumentation-vertexai/\">\n    <img src=\"https://badge.fury.io/py/opentelemetry-instrumentation-vertexai.svg\">\n</a>\n\nThis library allows tracing VertexAI prompts and completions sent with the official [VertexAI library](https://github.com/googleapis/python-aiplatform).\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install opentelemetry-instrumentation-vertexai\n```\n\n## Example usage\n\n```python\nfrom opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai import VertexAIInstrumentor\n\nVertexAIInstrumentor().instrument()\n```\n\n## Privacy\n\n**By default, this instrumentation logs prompts, completions, and embeddings to span attributes**. This gives you a clear visibility into how your LLM application is working, and can make it easy to debug and evaluate the quality of the outputs.\n\nHowever, you may want to disable this logging for privacy reasons, as they may contain highly sensitive data from your users. You may also simply want to reduce the size of your traces.\n\nTo disable logging, set the `TRACELOOP_TRACE_CONTENT` environment variable to `false`.\n\n```bash\nTRACELOOP_TRACE_CONTENT=false\n```\n\n"], "modules": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.utils", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.utils.dont_throw", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["A decorator that wraps the passed in function and logs exceptions instead of throwing them.\n\n@param func: The function to wrap\n@return: The wrapper function"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.version", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.version.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.config", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.config.Config", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.config.Config.exception_logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": []}], "exports": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai", "documentation": ["OpenTelemetry Vertex AI instrumentation"], "functions": [{"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.should_send_prompts", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.is_streaming_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "response", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vertexai.is_async_streaming_response", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "response", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "opentelemetry.instrumentation.vert